addToPossessed(address,address).details: this function is called usually by a tokenTempalte to add the coin in the list of those possessed by the user      after a transfer executed successfully      We check the balance is > 0 to avoid that some malevolent person/contract tries to add garbage to an unrelated      address.

params._possessor: the address of the wallet of which we have to update the possessedTokens array
params._tokenAddress: the address of the token to add

createToken(string,string,uint8,string,s.details: createToken creates a new TokenTemplate instance.

params._contractHash: the Hash of the PDF contract bound to this Token.
params._decimals: the decimals of the Token. Must be between 0 and 18 included.
params._hardCap: the total supply of the Token.
params._logoHash: the Hash of the image pointed by _logoURL, to ensure it has not been altered.
params._logoURL: the URL of the image representing the logo of the Token.

params._possessor: the address of which we want to know which tokens it posses

returns._0: the array containing the adresses of tokens possesed by the user

returns._0: the Token data in array form.
